<subSubSection id="CFAF3A4351019E4DE00035C359D7C302" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="note l">
<paragraph id="C4AD7ED4B635D7FB988CFFE6298A5718" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Note L.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D38E21566699DF43BCF86A7CC4196FAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<bibRefCitation id="BCF84F1DF39D3230EA142C8CB54B1480" author="Blume, CL" journalOrPublisher="Blumea" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/9225page/436/mode/1up" refId="B2" refString="Blume, CL, 1826. Bijdragen tot de flora van Nederlandsch Indie 17. Batavia, 1067-1169. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/9225page/436/mode/1up" title="Bijdragen tot de flora van Nederlandsch Indie 17. Batavia, 1067 - 1169." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/9225page/436/mode/1up" year="1826">Blume (1826)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="C79961FE928E19D608CB58B8DDD9CB1D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Mespilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mespilus spiralis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spiralis">
<emphasis id="14259B1219345606CC323D378595E777" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Mespilus spiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his book &quot;Bijdragen tot de flora van Nederlandsch Indië&quot;, noting that the original material on which it was based was collected from a plant introduced from China in Java. We found five sheets representing the duplicates from one collection, four of them from herbarium L and one of them from herbarium NY. It will be necessary for us to choose one of them as the lectotype. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="F6C6B57662EE45B30AA026718584F038" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103414page/11/mode/1up" refId="B36" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1976. Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Volume I: A-G. Regnum Vegetabile 137. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103414page/11/mode/1up" title="Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Volume I: A-G. Regnum Vegetabile 137. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103414page/11/mode/1up" year="1976">Stafleu and Cowan (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<normalizedToken id="2E0AEB1B9582107B49B8C59C62693B2F" originalValue="Blume’s">Blume's</normalizedToken>
original collections were deposited at L, second set at BO, and type mainly at L, but also at BO and P. One of the four duplicates deposited at L, therefore, will be a candidate for the lectotype. We designated the sheet (L0019710) in a better condition as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
